Place cream cheese, shredded cheese and mustard in food processor or blender container; cover. Process until well blended. Stir in chilies. Place on sheet of wax paper; shape into 4-inch oval to resemble a 'pinecone.' Insert almonds in rows to completely cover cream cheese mixture. Cover. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or until firm. Let stand at room temperature 15 min. before serving. Serve as a spread with crackers.